(secondQuint)Study of Allogeneic Bone Marrow Transplantation Following Cyclophosphamide and Radiotherapy in Patients With Fanconi's Anemia.

 PROTOCOL OUTLINE: Patients receive cyclophosphamide IV over 2 hours on day -6 through -3 and total lymphoid radiotherapy on day -1.

 Patients undergo allogeneic bone marrow transplantation on day 0.

 Patients are followed for at least 100 days.

